      ** +--------------------------------------+
      *
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      ** ¦ Arrays and Data Structures           ¦
      ** ¦ ==========================           ¦
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      *
      ** SE Diary Events for file update - file format
     D NwDEFilFmt    E DS                  EXTNAME(SEVSEDEPD)
      *
      ** SE Diary Events screen error indicators
     D SEESEDE       E DS                  EXTNAME(SEESEDEPD)
      *
      ** SE Diary Events screen details from incoming
      ** transaction - screen format
     D NwDE1ScnFmt   E DS                  EXTNAME(SESEDEPD)
      *
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      ** ¦ Declared variables                   ¦
      ** ¦ ==================                   ¦
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      *
      ** Index for arrays of error message ids, etc.
     D IDx             S              3P 0
      *
      ** Work parameters
     D ZFIELD          S             16A
     D ZADEC           S              1P 0
     D ZADIG           S              2P 0
     D ZALIGNok        S              1A
     D WConvRate       S             13P 8
      *
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      ** ¦ End of D-specs                       ¦
      ** ¦ ==============                       ¦
      ** +--------------------------------------+
      *
      *****************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      *
      ** +--- Start of Main processing -------------------------------+
      ** ¦                                                            ¦
      ** ¦ Initial processing is performed automatically.             ¦
      ** ¦ *INZSR is executed at program activation.                  ¦
      ** ¦                                                            ¦
      ** +------------------------------------------------------------+
      *
      *****************************************************************
      * MAIN PROCEDURE                                                *
      *****************************************************************
      *
      ** Initialise work variables.
     C                   EVAL      IDx = 0
     C                   EVAL      WConvRate = 0
      *
     C                   EXSR      SrConvRte
      *
      ** If an error has been found, set return code appropriately.
      ** Otherwise, update valid file fields.
      *
     C                   IF        OKCONR = 'N'
     C                   EVAL      RetCodeIn = 'ERROR'
     C                   ELSE
     C                   Z-ADD     WConvRate     S2SDCE
     C                   ENDIF
      *
     C                   RETURN
 
      *****************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      *                                                               *
      *  SrConvRte - Validate Conversion Exchange Rate                *
      *                                                               *
      *****************************************************************
 
     C     SrConvRte     BEGSR
      *
     C                   IF        DDCONR <> *BLANKS
      *
      ** Check for valid number.
     C                   EVAL      ZFIELD = *BLANKS
     C                   EVAL      ZFIELD = DDCONR
 
     C                   CALLB     'ZALIGN'
     C                   PARM      *BLANK        ZALIGNok
     C                   PARM                    ZFIELD
     C                   PARM      8             ZADEC
     C                   PARM      5             ZADIG
 
     C                   IF        ZALIGNok = 'N'
     C                   MOVE      'N'           OKCONR
     C                   ADD       1             IDx
     C                   MOVEL     'DDCONR'      FldNamXAr(IDx)
     C                   MOVEL     'SEA0345'     MsgIdXAr(IDx)
     C                   ELSE
     C                   MOVE      ZFIELD        WConvRate
     C                   ENDIF
 
     C                   ENDIF
 
     C                   ENDSR
 
      *****************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      *                                                               *
      *  *INZSR - Program Initialisation                              *
      *         - This subroutine runs automatically for program      *
      *           initialisation.                                     *
      *                                                               *
      *****************************************************************
      *
     C     *INZSR        BEGSR
      *
     C     *ENTRY        PLIST
      *
      ** INPUT
      ** =====
      *
      ** Return code
     C                   PARM                    RetCodeIn
      *
      ** SE Diary Events screen details from incoming
      ** transaction - screen format
     C                   PARM                    NwDE1ScnFmt
      *
      ** OUTPUT
      ** ======
      *
      ** Error fields/message IDs/message data (arrays) from/to caller
     C                   PARM                    FldNamXAr
     C                   PARM                    MsgIDXAr
     C                   PARM                    MsgDtaXAr
      *
      ** SE Diary Events screen error indicators
     C                   PARM                    SEESEDE
      *
      ** SE Diary Events for file update - file format
     C                   PARM                    NwDEFilFmt
      *
      ** Program, module and procedure names for dbase error processing
      ** ==============================================================
      ** The following /COPY sets these values.
      *
      /COPY ZACPYSRC,DBFIELDS
      *
     C                   ENDSR
      *
